% Author: Andrew Yates <andrewyates.name@gmail.com>
% Regression test for #6591: sparse-domain table support must honor interior holes.
% x has interval hull [1,3] but actual domain {1,3}; tuple (2,2) is invalid.
% The only support-consistent solution is therefore (x=1, y=1).
var {1, 3}: x :: output_var;
var 1..2: y :: output_var;
array [1..4] of int: tbl = [1, 1, 2, 2];
constraint fzn_table_int([x, y], tbl);
solve satisfy;
